main event: Three white, round UFOs were observed in formation climbing at a high speed in Coral Gables, Florida on April 6, 1954, and the conclusion was that there was insufficient data for evaluation.
interesting points: The UFO formation was described as reflecting light and climbing at a rapid speed.
The report indicates that the formation appeared to consist of 2 or 3 objects, each with a size of 30 degrees and spaced 20 degrees apart relative to the observer.
There was no evidence of the objects disappearing, and it was reported that there was no matter of disappearance.
The observation lasted only 3 seconds, suggesting a brief and sudden sighting.
The source of the report was the military, and the observer was a commercial pilot, adding credibility to the sighting.
sighted object: Three white, round UFOs in formation
witnesses: military personnel and a commercial pilot
